                <div class="carousel-wrapper">
                    <div class="faq-carousel" id="faqCarousel">
                        <div class="faq-card">
                            <h4>What is a TUI?</h4>
                            <p>
                                A Terminal User Interface. It's like a GUI, but
                                it runs entirely inside your command line! Think
                                retro hacker vibes meets modern design.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-card">
                            <h4>Who can participate?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Any teenager (18 or under) with a passion for
                                coding and building cool things. No prior TUI
                                experience required!
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-card">
                            <h4>Does it cost anything?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Absolutely nothing. You don't need expensive
                                hardware to make free software, and we even ship
                                you the hardware prizes globally for free.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-card">
                            <h4>Can I use other languages?</h4>
                            <p>
                                No. This YSWS aims to be Specific and Small. The
                                recomended stacks must to be followed to keep it
                                simple. You can use any starter-kit.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-card">
                            <h4>How do I submit?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Just build your project, open-source it on
                                GitHub, make a release, and submit the
                                repository link through email. You can deploy a
                                ssh server with Wish too, like <strong
                                    >$ ssh hackdash.dousec.org</strong
                                >
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <button class="carousel-nav next" aria-label="Next question"
                    >&gt;</button
                >
            </div>
